column9: AI training is a case where you need to look at the bigger picture: on the one hand, it's understandable that people don't want to see their work used in this way, but on the other hand, AI models require a lot of data, and one piece of work doesn't make up a significant part of the training. With that said, it should be possible to remove selected data from the database, even in case of web scraping, as this feature should be required by regulations such as the AI Act. If the author was able to know that their work had been used in the training of the data, removal should also be doable, or compensation relative to the proportion of the work used in the training could be considered.
